> Could CrowdStrike's network discovery scan be triggering something in krunkit/libkrun's virtio-net or gvproxy path that results in the power button event?

@Pepo48 I don't know if it's CrowdStrike in particular (though I'd say it's main suspect), but *something* (other than podman) is sending an HTTP POST to the random port used by the rest-uri, which is interpreted by krunkit as a request to shut down the machine. We're going to tighten the POST request parsing in krunkit and issue a new release today.

The `sshd-session[115025]: banner exchange: Connection from 192.168.127.1 port 17520: invalid format` is a hint that something is doing a local port scan (this is actually what drove me in the right direction).
